NSN DEFENDS AGAINST ATTACK BY WAGE THIEF:
Yesterday Sukh Auto owner, Sukhdeep Hunjan, tried to attack NSN members for protesting to demand the wages he stole. We drove him away. #Fateh #JangJaariHai
 
Over 100 workers & allies from the labour movement marched down Rutherford Rd in Brampton yesterday to demand workers’ pay from two wage thieves — Sukh Auto (Sukhdeep Hunjan) & Baba Dhaba (Mahabir Bhatth). 
 
STOLEN WAGES & VIOLENCE AGAINST WORKERS
 
Rupinder Singh is owed $4,020.34 in wages & vacation pay from Sukh Auto. When he went back to the office to demand his wages, Sukhdeep threatened to have him deported and hit Rupinder with a shovel. 
 
After Sukhdeep refused to pay, we protested in front of his shop on May 28 & supported Rupinder to file a labour claim. We then learned Sukhdeep filed a $515K defamation lawsuit against Rupinder and NSN. 
 
DEFENDING OURSELVES AGAINST CHOR SUKHDEEP HUNJAN
 
Yesterday we protested again in front of Sukh Auto with greater numbers. We saw that Sukhdeep had removed his business signs to escape the public shame. 
 
Near the end of the protest, Sukhdeep Hunjan came huffing and puffing into the crowd, smacked down the banner & attempted to violently snatch the mic from an NSN member explaining her family’s story of wage theft. We drove him away with our chants. A thief is no match for organized workers who will defend one another against the violence & disrespect of employers.
 
During the commotion, one of Sukh's supporters sucker punched an NSN member in the face, cutting his lip. Police attended the scene & arrested that person for assault. A white police sergeant then threatened to call the riot squad against NSN members & arrest every single one of us, including the elders & young children in attendance, even after we explained why we were protesting. We did not waver & continued our protest until all of us were free from police questioning.
